race.comment: GOLDEN OPERA (11) flew home last start in a 1200m maiden here and looks primed on the back of that effort. She jumped favourite there and reeled off some good splits to be 0.8L away at the finish. Will need some luck from the gate but has the class to shed the maiden tag. KIRRILY (9) missed by 1.2L last time out when dropping back to 1200m. She drops back in trip again today with the in-form apprentice on board, though she is lightly raced with some upside. Better run last start and she can build on that effort. TAPITLIKEIT'SSASSY (8) ran well fresh before a disappointing performance most recently over the 1232m trip. Dropping back in distance now may hold the key and she should be prominent from a good draw. Can bounce back to her best now. ARCTIC FOX (7) was solid over 1200m fresh and ticks a few boxes. HARLEQUIN PRANCER (5) has trialled well coming into this and is not to be discounted in her debut for the new yard.
